2671 static int HTPStateHasTxDetectState(void *alstate)
2672 {
2673  HtpState *htp_state = (HtpState *)alstate;
2674  return (htp_state->tx_with_detect_state_cnt > 0);
2675 }
2676 
2677 static DetectEngineState *HTPGetTxDetectState(void *vtx)
2678 {
2679  htp_tx_t *tx = (htp_tx_t *)vtx;
2680  HtpTxUserData *tx_ud = htp_tx_get_user_data(tx);
2681  return tx_ud ? tx_ud->de_state : NULL;
2682 }
2683 
2684 static int HTPSetTxDetectState(void *alstate, void *vtx, DetectEngineState *s)
2685 {
2686  HtpState *htp_state = (HtpState *)alstate;
2687  htp_tx_t *tx = (htp_tx_t *)vtx;
2688  HtpTxUserData *tx_ud = htp_tx_get_user_data(tx);
2689  if (tx_ud == NULL) {
2690  tx_ud = HTPMalloc(sizeof(*tx_ud));
2691  if (unlikely(tx_ud == NULL))
2692  return -ENOMEM;
2693  memset(tx_ud, 0, sizeof(*tx_ud));
2694  htp_tx_set_user_data(tx, tx_ud);
2695  }
2696  htp_state->tx_with_detect_state_cnt++;
2697  tx_ud->de_state = s;
2698  return 0;
2699 }
2700 
2701 static int HTPRegisterPatternsForProtocolDetection(void)
2702 {
2703  char *methods[] = { "GET", "PUT", "POST", "HEAD", "TRACE", "OPTIONS",
2704  "CONNECT", "DELETE", "PATCH", "PROPFIND", "PROPPATCH", "MKCOL",
2705  "COPY", "MOVE", "LOCK", "UNLOCK", "CHECKOUT", "UNCHECKOUT", "CHECKIN",
2706  "UPDATE", "LABEL", "REPORT", "MKWORKSPACE", "MKACTIVITY", "MERGE",
2707  "INVALID", "VERSION-CONTROL", "BASELINE-CONTROL", NULL};
2708  char *spacings[] = { "|20|", "|09|", NULL };
2709  char *versions[] = { "HTTP/0.9", "HTTP/1.0", "HTTP/1.1", NULL };
2710 
2711  uint methods_pos;
2712  uint spacings_pos;
2713  uint versions_pos;
2714  int register_result;
2715  char method_buffer[32] = "";
2716 
2717  /* Loop through all the methods ands spacings and register the patterns */
2718  for (methods_pos = 0; methods[methods_pos]; methods_pos++) {
2719  for (spacings_pos = 0; spacings[spacings_pos]; spacings_pos++) {
2720 
2721  /* Combine the method name and the spacing */
2722  snprintf(method_buffer, sizeof(method_buffer), "%s%s", methods[methods_pos], spacings[spacings_pos]);
2723 
2724  /* Register the new method+spacing pattern
2725  * 3 is subtracted from the length since the spacing is hex typed as |xx|
2726  * but the pattern matching should only be one char
2727  */
2728  register_result = AppLayerProtoDetectPMRegisterPatternCS(IPPROTO_TCP,
2729  ALPROTO_HTTP, method_buffer, strlen(method_buffer)-3, 0, STREAM_TOSERVER);
2730  if (register_result < 0) {
2731  return -1;
2732  }
2733  }
2734  }
2735 
2736  /* Loop through all the http verions patterns that are TO_CLIENT */
2737  for (versions_pos = 0; versions[versions_pos]; versions_pos++) {
2738  register_result = AppLayerProtoDetectPMRegisterPatternCS(IPPROTO_TCP,
2739  ALPROTO_HTTP, versions[versions_pos], strlen(versions[versions_pos]),
2740  0, STREAM_TOCLIENT);
2741  if (register_result < 0) {
2742  return -1;
2743  }
2744  }
2745 
2746  return 0;
2747 }
2748 
2749 /**
2750  * \brief Register the HTTP protocol and state handling functions to APP layer
2751  * of the engine.
2752  */
2753 void RegisterHTPParsers(void)
2754 {
2755  SCEnter();
2756 
2757  char *proto_name = "http";
2758 
2759  /** HTTP */
2760  if (AppLayerProtoDetectConfProtoDetectionEnabled("tcp", proto_name)) {
2761  AppLayerProtoDetectRegisterProtocol(ALPROTO_HTTP, proto_name);
2762  if (HTPRegisterPatternsForProtocolDetection() < 0)
2763  return;
2764  } else {
2765  SCLogInfo("Protocol detection and parser disabled for %s protocol",
2766  proto_name);
2767  return;
2768  }
2769 
2770  if (AppLayerParserConfParserEnabled("tcp", proto_name)) {
2771  AppLayerParserRegisterStateFuncs(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, HTPStateAlloc, HTPStateFree);
2772  AppLayerParserRegisterTxFreeFunc(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, HTPStateTransactionFree);
2773  AppLayerParserRegisterGetFilesFunc(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, HTPStateGetFiles);
2774  AppLayerParserRegisterGetStateProgressFunc(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, HTPStateGetAlstateProgress);
2775  AppLayerParserRegisterGetTxCnt(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, HTPStateGetTxCnt);
2776  AppLayerParserRegisterGetTx(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, HTPStateGetTx);
2777  AppLayerParserRegisterGetStateProgressCompletionStatus(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP,
2778  HTPStateGetAlstateProgressCompletionStatus);
2779  AppLayerParserRegisterHasEventsFunc(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, HTPHasEvents);
2780  AppLayerParserRegisterGetEventsFunc(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, HTPGetEvents);
2781  AppLayerParserRegisterGetEventInfo(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, HTPStateGetEventInfo);
2782 
2783  AppLayerParserRegisterTruncateFunc(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, HTPStateTruncate);
2784  AppLayerParserRegisterDetectStateFuncs(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP,
2785  HTPStateHasTxDetectState,
2786  HTPGetTxDetectState, HTPSetTxDetectState);
2787 
2788  AppLayerParserRegisterParser(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, STREAM_TOSERVER,
2789  HTPHandleRequestData);
2790  AppLayerParserRegisterParser(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, STREAM_TOCLIENT,
2791  HTPHandleResponseData);
2792  SC_ATOMIC_INIT(htp_config_flags);
2793  AppLayerParserRegisterParserAcceptableDataDirection(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, STREAM_TOSERVER);
2794  HTPConfigure();
2795  } else {
2796  SCLogInfo("Parsed disabled for %s protocol. Protocol detection"
2797  "still on.", proto_name);
2798  }
2799 #ifdef UNITTESTS
2800  AppLayerParserRegisterProtocolUnittests(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, HTPParserRegisterTests);
2801 #endif
2802 
2803  SCReturn;
2804 }

2823 /** \test Test case where chunks are sent in smaller chunks and check the
2824  * response of the parser from HTP library. */
2825 int HTPParserTest01(void)
2826 {
2827  int result = 1;
2828  Flow *f = NULL;
2829  uint8_t httpbuf1[] = "POST / HTTP/1.0\r\nUser-Agent: Victor/1.0\r\n\r\nPost"
2830  " Data is c0oL!";
2831  uint32_t httplen1 = sizeof(httpbuf1) - 1; /* minus the \0 */
2832  TcpSession ssn;
2833  HtpState *htp_state = NULL;
2834  int r = 0;
2835  AppLayerParserThreadCtx *alp_tctx = AppLayerParserThreadCtxAlloc();
2836 
2837  memset(&ssn, 0, sizeof(ssn));
2838 
2839  f = UTHBuildFlow(AF_INET, "1.2.3.4", "1.2.3.5", 1024, 80);
2840  if (f == NULL)
2841  goto end;
2842  f->protoctx = &ssn;
2843  f->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
2844 
2845  StreamTcpInitConfig(TRUE);
2846 
2847  uint32_t u;
2848  for (u = 0; u < httplen1; u++) {
2849  uint8_t flags = 0;
2850 
2851  if (u == 0)
2852  flags = STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_START;
2853  else if (u == (httplen1 - 1))
2854  flags = STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_EOF;
2855  else
2856  flags = STREAM_TOSERVER;
2857 
2858  SCMutexLock(&f->m);
2859  r = AppLayerParserParse(alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP, flags, &httpbuf1[u], 1);
2860  if (r != 0) {
2861  printf("toserver chunk %" PRIu32 " returned %" PRId32 ", expected"
2862  " 0: ", u, r);
2863  result = 0;
2864  SCMutexUnlock(&f->m);
2865  goto end;
2866  }
2867  SCMutexUnlock(&f->m);
2868  }
2869 
2870  htp_state = f->alstate;
2871  if (htp_state == NULL) {
2872  printf("no http state: ");
2873  result = 0;
2874  goto end;
2875  }
2876 
2877  htp_tx_t *tx = HTPStateGetTx(htp_state, 0);
2878  htp_header_t *h = htp_table_get_index(tx->request_headers, 0, NULL);
2879  if (strcmp(bstr_util_strdup_to_c(h->value), "Victor/1.0")
2880  || tx->request_method_number != HTP_M_POST ||
2881  tx->request_protocol_number != HTP_PROTOCOL_1_0)
2882  {
2883  printf("expected header value: Victor/1.0 and got %s: and expected"
2884  " method: POST and got %s, expected protocol number HTTP/1.0"
2885  " and got: %s \n", bstr_util_strdup_to_c(h->value),
2886  bstr_util_strdup_to_c(tx->request_method),
2887  bstr_util_strdup_to_c(tx->request_protocol));
2888  result = 0;
2889  goto end;
2890  }
2891 
2892 end:
2893  if (alp_tctx != NULL)
2894  AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
2895  StreamTcpFreeConfig(TRUE);
2896  if (htp_state != NULL)
2897  HTPStateFree(htp_state);
2898  UTHFreeFlow(f);
2899  return result;
2900 }

3344  uint32_t httplen2 = sizeof(httpbuf2) - 1; /* minus the \0 */
3345  TcpSession ssn;
3346  HtpState *http_state = NULL;
3347  AppLayerParserThreadCtx *alp_tctx = AppLayerParserThreadCtxAlloc();
3348 
3349  memset(&ssn, 0, sizeof(ssn));
3350 
3351  f = UTHBuildFlow(AF_INET, "1.2.3.4", "1.2.3.5", 1024, 80);
3352  if (f == NULL)
3353  goto end;
3354  f->protoctx = &ssn;
3355  f->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
3356 
3357  StreamTcpInitConfig(TRUE);
3358 
3359  SCMutexLock(&f->m);
3360  int r = AppLayerParserParse(alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP, STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_START,
3361  httpbuf1, httplen1);
3362  if (r != 0) {
3363  printf("toserver chunk 1 returned %" PRId32 ", expected 0: ", r);
3364  result = 0;
3365  SCMutexUnlock(&f->m);
3366  goto end;
3367  }
3368

3370  httplen2);
3371  if (r != 0) {
3372  printf("toclient chunk 2 returned %" PRId32 ", expected 0: ", r);
3373  result = 0;
3374  SCMutexUnlock(&f->m);
3375  goto end;
3376  }
3377  SCMutexUnlock(&f->m);
3378 
3379  http_state = f->alstate;
3380  if (http_state == NULL) {
3381  printf("no http state: ");
3382  result = 0;
3383  goto end;
3384  }
3385 
3386  htp_tx_t *tx = HTPStateGetTx(http_state, 0);
3387  htp_header_t *h = htp_table_get_index(tx->request_headers, 0, NULL);
3388  if (tx->request_method_number != HTP_M_GET ||
3389  h == NULL || tx->request_protocol_number != HTP_PROTOCOL_1_1)
3390  {
3391  printf("expected method M_GET and got %s: , expected protocol "
3392  "HTTP/1.1 and got %s \n", bstr_util_strdup_to_c(tx->request_method),
3393  bstr_util_strdup_to_c(tx->request_protocol));
3394  result = 0;
3395  goto end;
3396  }
3397 
3398  if (tx->response_status_number != 200 ||
3399  h == NULL || tx->request_protocol_number != HTP_PROTOCOL_1_1)
3400  {
3401  printf("expected response 200 OK and got %"PRId32" %s: , expected proto"
3402  "col HTTP/1.1 and got %s \n", tx->response_status_number,
3403  bstr_util_strdup_to_c(tx->response_message),
3404  bstr_util_strdup_to_c(tx->response_protocol));
3405  result = 0;
3406  goto end;
3407  }
3408 end:
3409  if (alp_tctx != NULL)
3410  AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
3411  StreamTcpFreeConfig(TRUE);
3412  if (http_state != NULL)
3413  HTPStateFree(http_state);
3414  UTHFreeFlow(f);
3415  return result;
3416 }

3420 int HTPParserTest07(void)

3428  int r = 0;

3430 
3431  memset(&ssn, 0, sizeof(ssn));
3432 
3433  f = UTHBuildFlow(AF_INET, "1.2.3.4", "1.2.3.5", 1024, 80);
3434  if (f == NULL)
3435  goto end;
3436  f->protoctx = &ssn;
3437  f->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
3438 
3439  StreamTcpInitConfig(TRUE);
3440 
3441  uint32_t u;
3442  for (u = 0; u < httplen1; u++) {
3443  uint8_t flags = 0;
3444 
3445  if (u == 0)
3446  flags = STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_START;
3447  else if (u == (httplen1 - 1))
3448  flags = STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_EOF;
3449  else
3450  flags = STREAM_TOSERVER;
3451 
3452  SCMutexLock(&f->m);
3453  r = AppLayerParserParse(alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP, flags, &httpbuf1[u], 1);
3454  if (r != 0) {

3465  printf("no http state: ");
3466  goto end;
3467  }
3468 
3469  uint8_t ref[] = "/awstats.pl?/migratemigrate = |";
3470  size_t reflen = sizeof(ref) - 1;
3471 
3472  htp_tx_t *tx = HTPStateGetTx(htp_state, 0);
3473  if (tx == NULL)
3474  goto end;
3475  HtpTxUserData *tx_ud = (HtpTxUserData *) htp_tx_get_user_data(tx);
3476  if (tx_ud != NULL && tx_ud->request_uri_normalized != NULL) {
3477  if (reflen != bstr_len(tx_ud->request_uri_normalized)) {
3478  printf("normalized uri len should be %"PRIuMAX", is %"PRIuMAX,
3479  (uintmax_t)reflen,
3480  (uintmax_t)bstr_len(tx_ud->request_uri_normalized));
3481  goto end;
3482  }
3483 
3484  if (memcmp(bstr_ptr(tx_ud->request_uri_normalized), ref,
3485  bstr_len(tx_ud->request_uri_normalized)) != 0)
3486  {
3487  printf("normalized uri \"");
3488  PrintRawUriFp(stdout, bstr_ptr(tx_ud->request_uri_normalized), bstr_len(tx_ud->request_uri_normalized));
3489  printf("\" != \"");
3490  PrintRawUriFp(stdout, ref, reflen);
3491  printf("\": ");
3492  goto end;
3493  }
3494  }
3495 
3496  result = 1;
3497 end:
3498  if (alp_tctx != NULL)
3499  AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
3500  StreamTcpFreeConfig(TRUE);
3501  if (htp_state != NULL)
3502  HTPStateFree(htp_state);
3503  UTHFreeFlow(f);
3504  return result;
3505 }

3919  }

4549 ";

5688

5691 
5692  uint8_t chunk1[] = "--e5a320f21416a02493a0a6f561b1c494\r\nContent-Disposition: form-data; name=\"uploadfile\"; filename=\"D2GUef.jpg\"\r";
5693  uint8_t chunk2[] = "POST /uri HTTP/1.1\r\nHost: hostname.com\r\nKeep-Alive: 115\r\nAccept-Charset: utf-8\r\nUser-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux i686; rv:9.0.1) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/9.0.1\r\nAccept: text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8\r\nConnection: keep-alive\r\nContent-length: 68102\r\nReferer: http://otherhost.com\r\nAccept-Encoding: gzip\r\nContent-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=e5a320f21416a02493a0a6f561b1c494\r\nCookie: blah\r\nAccept-Language: us\r\n\r\n--e5a320f21416a02493a0a6f561b1c494\r\nContent-Disposition: form-data; name=\"uploadfile\"; filename=\"D2GUef.jpg\"\r";
5694 
5695  int r = HtpBodyAppendChunk(&htud, &htud.request_body, (uint8_t *)chunk1, sizeof(chunk1)-1);
5696  BUG_ON(r != 0);
5697  r = HtpBodyAppendChunk(&htud, &htud.request_body, (uint8_t *)chunk2, sizeof(chunk2)-1);
5698  BUG_ON(r != 0);
5699

5705  goto end;
5706  }
5707 #ifdef PRINT
5708  printf("REASSCHUNK START: \n");
5709  PrintRawDataFp(stdout, chunks_buffer, chunks_buffer_len);
5710  printf("REASSCHUNK END: \n");
5711 #endif
5712 
5713  HtpRequestBodyHandleMultipart(&hstate, &htud, &tx, chunks_buffer, chunks_buffer_len);
5714 
5715  if (htud.request_body.content_len_so_far != 669) {
5716  printf("htud.request_body.content_len_so_far %"PRIu64": ", htud.request_body.content_len_so_far);
5717  goto end;
5718  }
5719 
5720  if (hstate.files_ts != NULL)
5721  goto end;
5722 
5723  result = 1;
5724 end:
5725  return result;
5726 }

5819 /** \test Test really long request, this should result in HTTP_DECODER_EVENT_REQUEST_FIELD_TOO_LONG */
5820 int HTPParserTest14(void)
5821 {
5822  int result = 0;
5823  Flow *f = NULL;
5824  char *httpbuf = NULL;
5825  size_t len = 18887;
5826  TcpSession ssn;
5827  HtpState *htp_state = NULL;
5828  int r = 0;
5829  char input[] = "\
5830 %YAML 1.1\n\
5831 ---\n\
5832 libhtp:\n\
5833 \n\
5834  default-config:\n\
5835  personality: IDS\n\
5836  double-decode-path: no\n\
5837  double-decode-query: no\n\
5838  request-body-limit: 0\n\
5839  response-body-limit: 0\n\
5840 ";
5841  AppLayerParserThreadCtx *alp_tctx = AppLayerParserThreadCtxAlloc();
5842 
5843  memset(&ssn, 0, sizeof(ssn));
5844 
5845  ConfCreateContextBackup();
5846  ConfInit();
5847  HtpConfigCreateBackup();
5848  ConfYamlLoadString(input, strlen(input));
5849  HTPConfigure();
5850 
5851  httpbuf = SCMalloc(len);
5852  if (unlikely(httpbuf == NULL))
5853  goto end;
5854  memset(httpbuf, 0x00, len);
5855 
5856  /* create the request with a longer than 18k cookie */
5857  strlcpy(httpbuf, "GET /blah/ HTTP/1.1\r\n"
5858  "Host: myhost.lan\r\n"
5859  "Connection: keep-alive\r\n"
5860  "Accept: */*\r\n"
5861  "User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/29.0.1547.76 Safari/537.36\r\n"
5862  "Referer: http://blah.lan/\r\n"
5863  "Accept-Encoding: gzip,deflate,sdch\r\nAccept-Language: en-US,en;q=0.8\r\n"
5864  "Cookie: ", len);
5865  size_t o = strlen(httpbuf);
5866  for ( ; o < len - 4; o++) {
5867  httpbuf[o] = 'A';
5868  }
5869  httpbuf[len - 4] = '\r';
5870  httpbuf[len - 3] = '\n';
5871  httpbuf[len - 2] = '\r';
5872  httpbuf[len - 1] = '\n';
5873 
5874  f = UTHBuildFlow(AF_INET, "1.2.3.4", "1.2.3.5", 1024, 80);
5875  if (f == NULL)
5876  goto end;
5877  f->protoctx = &ssn;
5878  f->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
5879 
5880  StreamTcpInitConfig(TRUE);
5881 
5882  uint32_t u;
5883  for (u = 0; u < len; u++) {
5884  uint8_t flags = 0;
5885 
5886  if (u == 0) flags = STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_START;
5887  else if (u == (len - 1)) flags = STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_EOF;
5888  else flags = STREAM_TOSERVER;
5889 
5890  SCMutexLock(&f->m);
5891  r = AppLayerParserParse(alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP, flags, (uint8_t *)&httpbuf[u], 1);
5892  if (u < 18294) { /* first 18294 bytes should result in 0 */
5893  if (r != 0) {
5894  printf("toserver chunk %" PRIu32 " returned %" PRId32 ", expected"
5895  " 0: ", u, r);
5896  result = 0;
5897  SCMutexUnlock(&f->m);
5898  goto end;
5899  }
5900  } else if (u == 18294UL) { /* byte 18294 should result in error */
5901  if (r != -1) {
5902  printf("toserver chunk %" PRIu32 " returned %" PRId32 ", expected"
5903  " -1: ", u, r);
5904  result = 0;
5905  SCMutexUnlock(&f->m);
5906  goto end;
5907  }
5908 
5909  /* break out, htp state is in error state now */
5910  SCMutexUnlock(&f->m);
5911  break;
5912  }
5913  SCMutexUnlock(&f->m);
5914  }
5915  htp_state = f->alstate;
5916  if (htp_state == NULL) {
5917  printf("no http state: ");
5918  goto end;
5919  }
5920 
5921  htp_tx_t *tx = HTPStateGetTx(htp_state, 0);
5922  if (tx == NULL || tx->request_method_number != HTP_M_GET || tx->request_protocol_number != HTP_PROTOCOL_1_1)
5923  {
5924  printf("expected method M_GET and got %s: , expected protocol "
5925  "HTTP/1.1 and got %s \n", bstr_util_strdup_to_c(tx->request_method),
5926  bstr_util_strdup_to_c(tx->request_protocol));
5927  goto end;
5928  }
5929 
5930  SCMutexLock(&f->m);
5931  AppLayerDecoderEvents *decoder_events = AppLayerParserGetEventsByTx(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP,f->alstate, 0);
5932  if (decoder_events == NULL) {
5933  printf("no app events: ");
5934  SCMutexUnlock(&f->m);
5935  goto end;
5936  }
5937  SCMutexUnlock(&f->m);
5938 
5939  if (decoder_events->events[0] != HTTP_DECODER_EVENT_REQUEST_FIELD_TOO_LONG) {
5940  printf("HTTP_DECODER_EVENT_REQUEST_FIELD_TOO_LONG not set: ");
5941  goto end;
5942  }
5943 
5944  result = 1;
5945 end:
5946  if (alp_tctx != NULL)
5947  AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
5948  StreamTcpFreeConfig(TRUE);
5949  if (htp_state != NULL)
5950  HTPStateFree(htp_state);
5951  UTHFreeFlow(f);
5952  if (httpbuf != NULL)
5953  SCFree(httpbuf);
5954  HTPFreeConfig();
5955  ConfDeInit();
5956  ConfRestoreContextBackup();
5957  HtpConfigRestoreBackup();
5958  return result;
5959 }
